data.TimesheetStatusEntry:
04/01
There was an error when running a certain club that has multiple members. The hold file created in the drill down report that will only display a certain number of members was causing problems when running the main report. I removed that portion of the code from the report.

04/02
There was a Prod bug with an RC job for DPR. I resolved that issue. There was a performance trick added to only display the members with upgrades/downgrades before checking the new draft amount and the old draft amount. This was done by creating a hold file with the members from another hold file that displays the members with upgrades/downgrades. However, when more than 1000 members were in the hold file, the where clause would break. I created a join to resolve this issue but there is a WebFocus issue with creating a join from a hold file.

data.TimesheetStatusEntry:
04/01
Resolving issues in the Accounting tab:
DRDR in ABC Internal tab – Resolved JS issue to hide the Queue button and displayed a popup alert when more than 50 clubs were selected. 

Resolving issues in the Club Account DT POS tab:
DT Stations Activity – The run and queue buttons are not working properly. Reworked some of the JS to try to get the report to run. There are 3 buttons, a run button, queue button, and excel (run) button. The excel and run button look the same and run the same report. I am not sure what the intent of having an extra button is for.

04/02
Resolving issues in the Club Account DT POS tab:
DT Stations Activity – When the run button and queue work, the date is being set to the default start and end date which at in 2015. The check all stations check box also stopped working. When the check all stations checkbox is clicked, the list is appending to the available stations list. New JS code for the check all stations checkbox. The report keeps showing no data which is masking an error message. 


04/03
There was an issue where the RC jobs that were previously working had stopped working. The issue was brought up to Tibco said the issue was -SET &ECHO=’ALL’. Removed all instances of -SET &ECHO = ON, ALL, NONE, OFF and added -*-SET &ECHO='ALL'; to all the procedures in these folders:
-	ABC Internal
-	Account Detail
-	Accounting


04/04
Continued to add -*-SET &ECHO='ALL'; to the remaining procedures in these folders:
-	Audit
-	Custom
-	PF Exclusive
-	Both common files, the one within the Club Reporting folder and the parent common file folder.

Wrote up a description for the issue in Member Billing for the Tibco support ticket.

Checked to see if there is a way to remove the Easy Selector Container that is being displayed when a tab is selected.

Created an export package with the procedure and all the master files associated with the report. 

Recreated the member billing issue using car file for the support ticket.

04/05 (3.5 hours):
Resolving issues in the Club Account DT POS tab:
DT Stations Activity – The report threw an error. The error was from the &STATION_NUM values containing ORs instead of , when it is being used in the where clause (WHERE…IN()). I added a function to change the ‘ OR ‘ to ‘,’. 

Resolved issues in the Daily tab:
Daily New Accounts – The report showed the wrong DOB because the a yy-mm-dd format was being used for the DOB. I found another date of birth field in the yyyy-mm-dd format. I used that instead of the 2 year field and displayed the date in the correct format.

04/01
Resolving issues in the Accounting tab:
DRDR in ABC Internal tab – Resolved JS issue to hide the Queue button and displayed a popup alert when more than 50 clubs were selected. 

Resolving issues in the Club Account DT POS tab:
DT Stations Activity – The run and queue buttons are not working properly. Reworked some of the JS to try to get the report to run. There are 3 buttons, a run button, queue button, and excel (run) button. The excel and run button look the same and run the same report. I am not sure what the intent of having an extra button is for.

04/02
Resolving issues in the Club Account DT POS tab:
DT Stations Activity – When the run button and queue work, the date is being set to the default start and end date which at in 2015. The check all stations check box also stopped working. When the check all stations checkbox is clicked, the list is appending to the available stations list. New JS code for the check all stations checkbox. The report keeps showing no data which is masking an error message. 


04/03
There was an issue where the RC jobs that were previously working had stopped working. The issue was brought up to Tibco said the issue was -SET &ECHO=’ALL’. Removed all instances of -SET &ECHO = ON, ALL, NONE, OFF and added -*-SET &ECHO='ALL'; to all the procedures in these folders:
-	ABC Internal
-	Account Detail
-	Accounting


04/04
Continued to add -*-SET &ECHO='ALL'; to the remaining procedures in these folders:
-	Audit
-	Custom
-	PF Exclusive
-	Both common files, the one within the Club Reporting folder and the parent common file folder.

Wrote up a description for the issue in Member Billing for the Tibco support ticket.

Checked to see if there is a way to remove the Easy Selector Container that is being displayed when a tab is selected.

Created an export package with the procedure and all the master files associated with the report. 

Recreated the member billing issue using car file for the support ticket.

04/05 (3.5 hours):
Resolving issues in the Club Account DT POS tab:
DT Stations Activity – The report threw an error. The error was from the &STATION_NUM values containing ORs instead of , when it is being used in the where clause (WHERE…IN()). I added a function to change the ‘ OR ‘ to ‘,’. 

Resolved issues in the Daily tab:
Daily New Accounts – The report showed the wrong DOB because the a yy-mm-dd format was being used for the DOB. I found another date of birth field in the yyyy-mm-dd format. I used that instead of the 2 year field and displayed the date in the correct format.
